  "prompt": "Is Masters in Public Health course included in SOL?",
  "response": "As of my last update, the School of Open Learning (SOL) at the University of Delhi primarily offers programs in the fields of Arts, Commerce, and Management at the undergraduate and postgraduate levels. The Master of Public Health (MPH) program is typically a specialized course that falls under the domain of health sciences and is usually offered by medical or public health institutions.\n\nTo confirm whether SOL now offers a Master in Public Health or if there have been any updates to their program offerings, I recommend checking the official SOL website or contacting their admissions office directly. Educational institutions often update their course offerings, and new programs might be introduced based on demand and institutional capacity.\n\nIf you're looking for an MPH program in India, you might also want to explore other universities that specialize in health sciences, such as:\n\n1. **All India Institute of Medical Sciences (AIIMS)**\n2. **Tata Institute of Social Sciences (TISS)**\n3. **Public Health Foundation of India (PHFI)**\n4. **Indian Institute of Public Health (IIPH)**\n\nThese institutions are well-known for their public health programs and might offer the course you're interested in.",
